<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>floor-walker • walk the floor</xh5><p> <i>floor-walker—</i>a person employed in a large store to direct customers, oversee sales, etc.: I next went into a store further up Broadway. When I entered I approached the <u>floor-walker</u>. </p><p><i>walk the floor—</i>pace nervously across the floor, especially while waiting: While Bill waited for news of the operation, he <u>walked the floor</u> for hours on end.</p> </entry>
